# Project: ShotenX AI · Lightning Agent Economy (Frontend)

This is the Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack) frontend for an AI agent
marketplace with L402 Lightning payments. The Express backend lives in a
sibling repo at `/Users/engineer/shotenx_ai_backend` (port 8080).

## Architecture (do not break)

- Most backend calls go through `lib/api.ts` using the `/backend/*` rewrite
  (`proxy.ts`). NEVER call the backend host directly from client code.
- Exception: `api.queryPaidAgent` must call **same-origin**
  `POST /api/premium/agent-query` (Next `app/api/premium/agent-query/route.ts`).
  That route issues invoices via the backend and runs Agentverse via
  `POST /api/agent-chat` on this app — Express does not implement
  `/api/premium/agent-query`, so proxying it would 404.
- Auto-router L402 flow: `app/agent-chat/page.tsx` →
  `api.autoRunSmartAgentWithPayment` → `POST /api/smart-auto-run` → backend
  `POST /api/agents/auto-run`.
- Agentverse paid chat: `PaidAgentConversation` / `app/agent/[agentAddress]` →
  `api.queryPaidAgent` → `app/api/premium/agent-query` (pay) → `app/api/agent-chat`
  (uagent-client query after proof).
- Live Lightning payment ledger: `app/(dashboard)/transactions/page.tsx` merges
  `api.getPaymentLogs()` (Node backend) with `public.transactions` in Supabase
  (`lib/user-ledger.ts`). Apply `supabase/migrations/20260426120000_services_and_transactions.sql`
  in the Supabase SQL Editor so RLS-backed `services` + `transactions` work.

## Global rules

- NEVER break existing routes, payment timelines, or the wallet badge.
- ALWAYS extend `lib/api.ts` (don't ad-hoc fetch backend endpoints).
- Use Tailwind utility classes; the project already has dark mode.
- Use functional React components and hooks only.
- Inputs validated client-side AND server-side (server is source of truth).
- Wrap async UI calls and surface errors via `useToast` from
  `components/theme-provider.tsx`.

## Forbidden

- No hardcoded backend hosts (`http://localhost:8080`, etc.) outside `.env`.
- No Composio code paths (removed from this project).
- No mocked transaction/agent data in dashboards — use live backend feeds.
- No `console.log` left in committed UI code.
